						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Hence while permenantly disabling your lockout chip is the easiest mod, it actually prevents certain games from running correctly. </div>
<br />
<br />No unlicensed cartridge I have tried fails to work in my lockout-chip less Famicom AV, and that includes boards from American Video Entertainment/S.E.I., Tengen, Color Dreams/Bunch Games/Wisdom Tree and Camerica/Codemasters (including a switchless Aladdin Deck Enhancer.)  
<br />
<br />(I haven't tried and don't own any of the truly rare carts from Active Enterprises, Panesian or Caltron/Myriad.)  
<br />
<br />If you are among the lucky few who possess any of these rare games, I'm sure you will can afford an early toaster.
<br />
<br />But according to the schematic, why not cut the reset pin of the console lockout chip?  That way, even if the game doesn't work with the lockout chip, the lockout chip cannot negatively affect the running of the game by toggling the reset line once per second.</div>

					
